Very coarse sand contains common to abundant shell fragments and rare whole macrofossils, including a variety of bivalves and gastropods. ~Whole bivalve at Section 4, 18-22 cm.  Portions of the very coarse sand exhibit convolute bedding, especially as defined by folded and deformed thin interbeds of sandy mud.  
The silty mud varies from massive to medium-laminated.  Some intervals of the silty mud exhibit convolute or inclined lamination.
